        </div>
        <div id="content">
            <section id="content1">
                <div class="row tips">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">
                        <h1 class="mb-1">Save Water While Bathing</h1>
                        <p>When taking a bath, just fill the tub halfway to keep water from spilling over. First
                            plug the
                            drain and set the temperature as it fills the tank.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <img src="images/bathing.jpg" alt="" class="tips-image">

                    </div>

                </div>

                <div class="row tips">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <h1 class="mb-1">Place a bucket in the shower</h1>
                        <p>When waiting for the water to warm up, place a bucket in the tub and use the water you
                            catch for
                            watering plants, splashing the toilet or washing.</p>

                    </div>

                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <img src="images/bucket-in-shower.jpg" alt="" class="tips-image">

                    </div>

                </div>


                <div class="row tips">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <h1 class="mb-1">Reduce your shower time</h1>
                        <p>When you’re losing track of time, carry a radio into the bathroom and time yourself with
                            how many
                            songs you play when you’re in.</p>

                    </div>

                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <img src="images/showerTime.jpg" alt="" class="tips-image">

                    </div>

                </div>



                <div class="row tips">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <h1 class="mb-1">Re-use Towels</h1>
                        <p>The towel you use to dry after a shower does not need to be laundered after each use, so
                            hang it
                            up and re-use it instead.</p>

                    </div>

                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <img src="images/towel.jpg" alt="" class="tips-image">

                    </div>

                </div>


                <div class="row tips">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">


                        <h1 class="mb-1">Install a low-flow showerhead</h1>
                        <p>It may cost you a bit of money up front but your efforts to save water will save you
                            money down
                            the road.</p>

                    </div>

                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <img src="images/showerhead.png" alt="" class="tips-image">

                    </div>
                </div>


            </section>
            <section id="content2">
                <div class="row tips">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <h1 class="mb-1">Check your toilets and faucets for leaks</h1>
                        <p>If you have a small leak in your toilet or a faucet, you could be losing hundreds of
                            gallons of water per day.</p>

                    </div>

                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <img src="images/leak.jpg" alt="" class="tips-image">

                    </div>

                </div>

                <div class="row tips">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">
                        <h1 class="mb-1">Get a low-flow toilet</h1>


                        <p>Flushing is the biggest water hog in the house. Older, conventional toilets can use 20 to
                            28 litres per flush, but low-flow models use as little as 7 litres.
                        </p>

                    </div>

                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <img src="images/low-flow-toilet.jpg" alt="" class="tips-image">

                    </div>


                </div>


                <div class="row tips">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">
                        <h1 class="mb-1">Dual flush toilets</h1>

                        <p>A dual flush toilet drives lower water usage in your home, thereby saving money on your
                            monthly water bill while being environment friendly.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <img src="images/dual-flush.jpg" alt="" class="tips-image">

                    </div>

                </div>



                <div class="row tips">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <h1 class="mb-1">Put a filled plastic bottle inside the tank</h1>

                        <p>It will help reduce the amount of water used per flush (if you can’t replace your higher
                            volume toilet).</p>

                    </div>

                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <img src="images/showerhead.png" alt="" class="tips-image">

                    </div>


                </div>


            </section>

            <section id="content3">
                <div class="row tips">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <h1 class="mb-1">Reuse cooking water</h1>
                        <p>Don’t let the grey water from boiling pasta and veggies go to waste. Instead of dumping it
                            down the drain, why not use it to water your garden?</p>

                    </div>

                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <img src="images/cookingwater.jpeg" alt="" class="tips-image">

                    </div>

                </div>

                <div class="row tips">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <h1 class="mb-1">Capture running water</h1>
                        <p>Instead of letting precious water run down the drain, capture it in a bucket while waiting
                            for the temperature to change.</p>

                    </div>

                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <img src="images/runningwater.jpg" alt="" class="tips-image">

                    </div>

                </div>


                <div class="row tips">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <h1 class="mb-1">Use appropriate pot sizes</h1>
                        <p>Unless you really need to, don’t be tempted to use big pots and pans. Large pots tend to
                            require more cooking water than is necessary.</p>

                    </div>

                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <img src="images/pot-size.jpg" alt="" class="tips-image">

                    </div>

                </div>



                <div class="row tips">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <h1 class="mb-1">Don’t let your faucets needlessly run</h1>
                        <p>While cooking, refrain from keeping your faucets open which will help you save lots of water.
                        </p>

                    </div>

                    
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <img src="images/needless-running.jpeg" alt="" class="tips-image">

                    </div>

                </div>

            </section>
            <section id="content4">
                <div class="row tips">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                    <h1 class="mb-1">Wash your jeans less</h1>
                    <p>Washing them a lot will wear them out more quickly. Consider airing them out or even putting
                        them in the freezer to freshen them up.</p>

                    </div>
                        <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                            <img src="images/wash-jeans.jpg" alt="" class="tips-image">

                        </div>

                </div>


                <div class="row tips">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                    <h1 class="mb-1">Run full loads</h1>
                    <p>Use your machine only when the load is full. This will help you to save loads of water more
                        efficiently.</p>

                    </div>

                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                        <img src="images/full-load.jpg" alt="" class="tips-image">

                    </div>
                    

                </div>

                <div class="row tips">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                    <h1 class="mb-1">Use front-loading washing machines</h1>
                    <p>They are usually the most water efficient, using up to 50% less water.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12">

                    <img src="images/front-loading.jpg" alt="" class="tips-image">

                </div>

                </div>

            </section>

            <section id="content5">
